 213:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      *** Deinitialization of ADC ***
 214:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      ============================================================
 215:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      [..]
 216:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 217:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     (#) Disable the ADC interface
 218:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****       (++) ADC clock can be hard reset and disabled at RCC top level.
 219:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****         (++) Hard reset of ADC peripherals
 220:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****              using macro __ADCx_FORCE_RESET(), __ADCx_RELEASE_RESET().
 221:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****         (++) ADC clock disable
 222:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****              using the equivalent macro/functions as configuration step.
 223:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****              (+++) Example:
 224:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****                    Into HAL_ADC_MspDeInit() (recommended code location) or with
 225:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****                    other device clock parameters configuration:
 226:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****                (+++) PeriphClkInit.PeriphClockSelection = RCC_PERIPHCLK_ADC
 227:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****                (+++) PeriphClkInit.AdcClockSelection = RCC_ADCPLLCLK2_OFF
 228:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****                (+++) HAL_RCCEx_PeriphCLKConfig(&PeriphClkInit)
 229:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 230:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     (#) ADC pins configuration
 231:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****          (++) Disable the clock for the ADC GPIOs
 232:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****               using macro __HAL_RCC_GPIOx_CLK_DISABLE()
 233:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 234:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     (#) Optionally, in case of usage of ADC with interruptions:
 235:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****          (++) Disable the NVIC for ADC
 236:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****               using function HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ(ADCx_IRQn)
 237:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 238:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     (#) Optionally, in case of usage of DMA:
 239:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****          (++) Deinitialize the DMA
 240:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****               using function HAL_DMA_Init().
 241:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****          (++) Disable the NVIC for DMA
 242:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****               using function HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ(DMAx_Channelx_IRQn)
 243:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 244:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     [..]
 245:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     
 246:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     *** Callback registration ***
 247:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     =============================================
 248:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     [..]
 249:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 250:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      The compilation flag USE_HAL_ADC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS, when set to 1,
 251:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 252:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      Use Functions HAL_ADC_RegisterCallback()
 253:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      to register an interrupt callback.
 254:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     [..]
 255:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 256:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      Function HAL_ADC_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 257:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) ConvCpltCallback               : ADC conversion complete callback
 258:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) ConvHalfCpltCallback           : ADC conversion DMA half-transfer callback
 259:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) LevelOutOfWindowCallback       : ADC analog watchdog 1 callback
ARM GAS  C:\WINDOWS\ccjOB5ii.s 			page 6


 260:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) ErrorCallback                  : ADC error callback
 261:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) InjectedConvCpltCallback       : ADC group injected conversion complete callback
 262:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) MspInitCallback                : ADC Msp Init callback
 263:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) MspDeInitCallback              : ADC Msp DeInit callback
 264:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 265:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      and a pointer to the user callback function.
 266:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     [..]
 267:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 268:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      Use function HAL_ADC_UnRegisterCallback to reset a callback to the default
 269:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      weak function.
 270:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     [..]
 271:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 272:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      HAL_ADC_UnRegisterCallback takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 273:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      and the Callback ID.
 274:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 275:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) ConvCpltCallback               : ADC conversion complete callback
 276:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) ConvHalfCpltCallback           : ADC conversion DMA half-transfer callback
 277:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) LevelOutOfWindowCallback       : ADC analog watchdog 1 callback
 278:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) ErrorCallback                  : ADC error callback
 279:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) InjectedConvCpltCallback       : ADC group injected conversion complete callback
 280:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) MspInitCallback                : ADC Msp Init callback
 281:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****        (+) MspDeInitCallback              : ADC Msp DeInit callback
 282:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      [..]
 283:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 284:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      By default, after the HAL_ADC_Init() and when the state is HAL_ADC_STATE_RESET
 285:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 286:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      examples HAL_ADC_ConvCpltCallback(), HAL_ADC_ErrorCallback().
 287:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are
 288:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      reset to the legacy weak functions in the HAL_ADC_Init()/ HAL_ADC_DeInit() only when
 289:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 290:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     [..]
 291:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 292:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      If MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_ADC_Init()/ HAL_ADC_DeInit()
 293:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand) whatever the state.
 294:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      [..]
 295:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 296:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_ADC_STATE_READY state only.
 297:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit functions that can be registered/unregistered
 298:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      in HAL_ADC_STATE_READY or HAL_ADC_STATE_RESET state,
 299:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 300:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****     [..]
 301:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 302:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      Then, the user first registers the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 303:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      using HAL_ADC_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_ADC_DeInit()
 304:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      or HAL_ADC_Init() function.
 305:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      [..]
 306:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
 307:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      When the compilation flag USE_HAL_ADC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 308:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all callbacks
 309:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****      are set to the corresponding weak functions.
 310:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****   
 311:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****   @endverbatim
 312:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c ****   */
 313:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_adc.c **** 
